  "body": "From https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/11942#issuecomment-136467907\nAssymetric update ex: Replace an rc A with 5 replicas with an rc B with 7 replicas (old and new RCs have different replica sizes).\nRollingUpdate rollback rolls back to old RC, but scales it up to the number of replicas, the new RC had (for ex it will rollback to rc A but with 7 replicas).\n\nWe need to fix that.\nWith https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/11942, we now add an \"original-replicas\" annotation to oldRC, which we should use.\n\ncc @ironcladlou @ghodss \n",
